  "abstract": "These varieties were developed at ICRISAT Asia Center (IAC) , Patancheru, India. ICGV 92196 originated from the cross Chico x ICGV 86052; ICGV 92206 from Chico x ICGV 86533; ICGV 92234 from ICGV 86162 x Shuikouyazai; and ICGV 92243 originated from ICGV 86093 x ICG 261. Chico is a short-duration Spanish germplasm line released in the USA. ICGV 86052, I C GV 86162, and I C GV 86093 are high-yielding Spanish varieties developed at IAC. ICGV 86533 is an insect-pest resistant variety developed at IAC. Shuikouyazai is a Spanish landrace from China, and ICG 261 is a Valencia line from Argentina.",
